From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Entrpi <entrpi@proton.me>
Date: Sun, 8 Feb 2026 13:10:25 +1100
Subject: [PATCH] PCI: sky1: Add MCFG quirk for CIX Sky1 Cadence PCIe
 controllers
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Add ACPI ECAM quirk for CIX Sky1 (CD8180) PCIe controllers under ACPI
boot. Firmware brings links up but leaves controllers partially
configured — missing RC BAR setup for I/O windows, missing TLP
filtering, and HW power state transitions enabled.

The quirk provides custom ECAM ops matched via MCFG OEM ID "CIXTEK" /
Table ID "SKY1EDK2". The init callback finds each controller's
companion CIXH2020 ACPI device, maps register banks, performs
controller register initialization (RC BAR config, device control,
ASPM, TLP filter, Gen3/Gen4 presets), and programs outbound ATU
entries for MEM and I/O windows.

Includes supporting changes:
- pci-acpi.c: MMIO window trim, D-state disable, I/O port injection
- quirks.c: D3/ASPM quirks for Cadence bridge devices
- setup-res.c: Silence I/O assignment failures gracefully
- phy-cix-usbdp.c: Skip PHY reset under ACPI boot

Known issue: link quiesce/retrain cycle causes WiFi (x2 controller)
link instability — needs further investigation.
